The course is meant for students whose mother tongue is Estonian.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide future primary teachers with the holistic view of the system Estonian ortography and phonetics and integrate theoretical knowledge with didactic skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student can correctly pronounce Estonian sounds, diphtongs and consonants as well as correct students' pronunciation; can write in correct Estonian, considering the orthographic rules; will recognise common mistakes in primary students' language use; can analyse and correct mistakes and explain the rules to students.
